# Versioned RAG System — Tier 3 Evaluation Metrics

## Background

The project already has a working RAG evaluation pipeline for Tier 1 (retrieval) and Tier 2 (generation quality) metrics operating on a movie ChromaDB database. We now extend it with a **Versioned RAG** subsystem that ingests Bootstrap release `.md` files from `versioned_articles/` (v5.2.3 → v5.3.5), manages document versions in SQLite + ChromaDB, and measures four Tier 3 metrics specific to temporal/versioned knowledge bases.

## Architecture

```
versioned_articles/*.md  →  VersionedKBManager (parses & ingests)
                              ├── SQLite  (version_metadata.db)  — tracks doc_id, version, timestamp, checksum
                              └── ChromaDB collection ("versioned_kb")  — stores embeddings per chunk

VersionedRAGRetriever   →  queries ChromaDB by version-aware filter + ranks results
VersionedRAGGenerator   →  wraps existing AnswerGenerator / FallbackLLM
run_versioned_eval.py   →  orchestrates metrics and prints tables
```

## Tier 3 Metrics Definitions

| Metric | Description | How Computed |
|---|---|---|
| **Temporal Leakage Rate** | % of queries that return chunks from a *newer* version than the query's target version | For each query pinned to a specific version, check if any retrieved chunk has a `version_date > target_date`. Fraction of such queries = leakage rate. |
| **Change Detection Accuracy** | How accurately the system flags "changed" content between consecutive versions | Compare content checksums (SHA-256) between consecutive version pairs. True Changed = checksum differs. Detected Changed = cosine similarity of embeddings drops below threshold. F1 of detected vs true. |
| **Update Efficiency** | Ratio of chunks actually re-embedded (re-indexed) vs. total chunks when a new version is ingested | Only changed/new chunks should be re-embedded. `updated_chunks / total_chunks` per version ingestion. Lower = more efficient (only updated what changed). |
| **p50 / p95 / p99 Query Latency** | Percentile latency of versioned retrieval across all queries | Collect wall-clock time for each retrieve call, compute numpy percentiles. |

