## Data Flow (versioned_articles → output)

```
1. VersionedKBManager.ingest_all()
   └─ For each .md file:
       a. Parse version string (e.g., "v5.3.1") and release date from filename/content
       b. Chunk content into ~300-token paragraphs
       c. Compute SHA-256 checksum of each chunk
       d. Compare against SQLite for prior version of same logical section
       e. Re-embed only NEW or CHANGED chunks (update_efficiency tracking)
       f. Upsert into ChromaDB with metadata: {version, version_date, source_file, checksum}
       g. Record in SQLite: (chunk_id, version, version_date, checksum, changed_flag)

2. VersionedRAGRetriever.retrieve(query, target_version=None)
   └─ Dense similarity search in ChromaDB
   └─ If target_version given: filter where metadata.version == target_version (strict) 
      OR filter where metadata.version_date <= target_version_date (inclusive history)
   └─ Return docs + latency

3. run_versioned_eval.py runs 6 queries across versions → computes all Tier 3 metrics
```

